benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/export/{accountId} - Export account data

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC06, TC14, TC15, TC08) demonstrate successful 200 responses with proper content-type (application/octet-stream) and valid export archives.

GET Method - Query Parameters/Path and Headers validation: Tests cover valid/invalid accountId formats (TC04, TC11), missing required header (TC03), and presence of required headers (TC01, TC02, TC15).
GET Method - Authorization: Includes test for unauthorized access (TC18) leading to 401, and tests ensuring authorized access when token is provided.

GET Method - Error Handling: Covers a range of error responses (400 for bad input in TC03/TC04/TC11, 404 for not found in TC05/TC07/TC12, 500 for service unavailability in TC10, 504 for timeout in TC17).
GET Method - Unsupported HTTP Method: TC16 verifies 405 Method Not Allowed for POST.
gaps: Empty Response: No scenario explicitly testing an empty export payload or no data available scenario (empty archive).
Pagination: No tests covering pagination behavior for large datasets (though TC08 tests large data size, it does not verify any pagination of results).
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling of rapid successive requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client-side caching semantics.
Authority-rich negative tests: While 401 is covered, there is limited coverage for 403 Forbidden scenarios or malformed/expired tokens beyond 401.
recommendations: Add an Empty Data/No Data scenario to confirm proper handling when an account export yields no data.
Introduce Pagination tests if export payloads can be chunked or paginated for very large datasets, and verify correct boundaries and performance.
Add Rate Limiting tests to ensure system stability under burst traffic (e.g., multiple rapid requests).
Add Caching tests to verify presence and correctness of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and validation behavior on subsequent requests.
Expand authorization tests to include 403 Forbidden scenarios and token expiry/malformed token cases to ensure proper access control handling.
